<li id="cite_note-121"><b><a href="#cite_ref-121" title="">^</a></b> Confusion of the two names is witnessed to as late as the end of the second century: in 197, <a href="/wiki/Tertullian" title="Tertullian">Tertullian</a> commented that those who attacked the Christians commonly mispronounced the name as "Chrestian" (<a href="http://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/anf03.iv.viii.i.iii.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ccel.org/ccel/schaff/anf03.iv.viii.i.iii.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Ad Nationes</i>, book I, chapter III</a>).</li>
